World Wrestling Entertainment tweeted to say it was "saddened" to learn of his death, after reports of his ill health emerged at the weekend. His friend and former wrestling partner Kevin Nash said on Monday Scott's life support would be "discontinued" once his family was "in place". "I have to prepare my life without him in the present," Kevin wrote on Monday. "I've been blessed to have a friend that took me at face value and I him." Scott, 63 emerged in the 1990s alongside the likes of Hulk Hogan and Sean 'X-Pac' Waltman. He was inducted into the WWE Hall of Fame in 2014.